Definition.WordDefinition:
Finally \Fi"nal*ly\, adv. 1. At the end or conclusion; ultimately; lastly; as, the contest was long, but the Romans finally conquered. [1913 Webster]
Whom patience finally must crown. --Milton. [1913 Webster]
2. Completely; beyond recovery. [1913 Webster]
Not any house of noble English in Ireland was utterly destroyed or finally rooted out. --Sir J. Davies. [1913 Webster]

finally adv 1: after a long period of time or an especially long delay; "at length they arrived" [syn: {eventually}, {at length}] 2: the item at the end; "last, I'll discuss family values" [syn: {last}, {lastly}, {in conclusion}] 3: as the end result of a succession or process; "ultimately he had to give in"; "at long last the winter was over" [syn: {ultimately}, {in the end}, {at last}, {at long last}]
